## Description
Fixes iOS 100vh viewport trap by using dynamic viewport height units (dvh) with fallbacks.

## Problem
- iOS Safari changes viewport height when address bar appears/disappears
- Fixed vh units don't account for this, causing content to be cut off
- Affects hero sections, modals, and full-height containers

## Solution
- Replace `min-h-[80vh]` with `min-h-[80vh] supports-[height:100dvh]:min-h-[80dvh]`
- Add `overscroll-behavior-contain` to prevent elastic bounce during scroll
- Update all vh-based heights in modals and full-screen components

## Impact
- Hero video no longer cuts off on iOS when scrolling
- Modals stay visible with keyboard open
- Better mobile experience on all iOS devices

## Browser Support
- iOS Safari 15.4+
- Chrome 108+
- Fallback to vh for older browsers
